<HEADLINE> Avalanche 5, Stars 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Milan Hejduk and Ville Nieminen scored third-
period goals as the Colorado Avalanche opened the exhibition season
with a 5-3 victory over the Dallas Stars on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   Hejduk made it 4-3 with a short-handed goal, converting a pass
from Joe Sakic at 2:36 of the final period. Nieminen beat goalie
Rick Tabaracci off a rebound at 8:33.
</P>
<P>
   Martin Skoula, Joel Prpic and Jared Aulin added goals for the
Avalanche, who were eliminated by Dallas in the Western Conference
finals last season. David Aebischer made 15 saves.
</P>
<P>
   Jonathan Sim, Blake Sloan and Tyler Bouck scored for the Stars,
who were 1-for-11 on the power play.
</P>
</TEXT>
