<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 02:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gore concert and MTV Video Music Awards: More in common than you might think </HEADLINE>
By DEEPTI HAJELA
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) - It boggles the mind, but the concert honoring
Vice President Al Gore and Sen. Joseph Lieberman had more in common
with the 2000 MTV Video Music Awards than you might have thought
possible.
</P>
<P>
   There was location - the events were held, a week apart, at
Radio City Music Hall. And there was Lenny Kravitz - the musician
who presented an award for MTV and performed for the Democrats.
</P>
<P>
   ''No matter where I go and no matter what it is that I'm doing
my whole thing is about preserving life and that's what I sing
about and that's what I'm here to represent,'' Kravitz said before
Thursday night's concert for Gore and Lieberman.
</P>
<P>
   OK, but could this be as fun as the Sept. 7 MTV awards, where he
presented an award with model Gisele Bundchen?
</P>
<P>
   ''This is very interesting, very interesting,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday night's concert was a fund-raiser for the Democratic
National Committee that featured performers including Jon Bon Jovi,
Sheryl Crow, and Crosby, Stills and Nash. Hosts included Julia
Roberts, John Leguizamo, and Salma Hayek.
</P>
<P>
   Both events also had controversy. Gore came under Republican
fire on Thursday for consorting with entertainment industry types
(the concert was put together for the Democrats under the
supervision of movie mogul Harvey Weinstein) in the same week that
he criticized that industry for marketing violence and adult
material to children.
</P>
<P>
   At MTV, controversy surrounded rapper Eminem over the content of
his song lyrics. Before the show, members of the Gay and Lesbian
Alliance Against Defamation protested MTV's support of Eminem,
saying his lyrics promote violence against homosexuals and women.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, there were differences between the two events, most
noticeably, the fashion. Clothing at the MTV awards was about the
revealing and the risque. Lil' Kim wore orange plastic, Christina
Aguilera's dress had a huge cutout in the center that showed off a
thong strap, and Jennifer Lopez wore hip-hugger pants.
</P>
<P>
   There were no major displays of skin at the Democrat concert.
Roberts was covered up in a black jacket and tan pants, and k.d.
lang was in what looked like a jogging suit. Laura Dern wore black
leather, but the dress went to her feet and she wore a black
knitted shawl over it.
</P>
<P>
   The biggest difference might have been the media coverage. When
MTV took over Radio City, hordes of journalists from around the
world converged on the Big Apple, jostling for space in three-deep
lines.
</P>
<P>
   At Thursday's concert, there was plenty of standing room in the
media pen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
