<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Turn Lower To Begin Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Wall Street has both earnings news and economic
data to study this morning. In early trading, the Dow Jones
industrial average is down 2 points. Losing issues on the New York
Stock Exchange hold a 2-to-1 lead over gainers. The Nasdaq
composite index is off 22 points and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index is down 2 points.
</P>
<P>
   On the earnings front, Oracle, Adobe Systems and Nike have all
posted better-than-expected quarterly results. At the same time,
Maytag has warned that upcoming results will fall short of earlier
estimates.
</P>
<P>
   On the economic front, consumer prices fell in August for the
first time in 14 years, as gasoline prices declined. But,
economists say that's misleading because gas prices have already
turned higher this month.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-09-15-00 0945 </TRAILER>
