<HEADLINE> Betsey Johnson: Implant saved my life  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Funk fashion queen Betsey Johnson says a breast
implant may have saved her life.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson, 58, said Thursday that one of her implants collapsed,
and she went to have them removed just before Christmas. It was
then that doctors discovered a small, cancerous tumor. She had a
lumpectomy to remove it and underwent radiation as well.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson - who dazzled the fashion world in the 1960s with her
clear vinyl dresses, silver motorcycle suits and other inexpensive,
groovy fashions - spread the news at an event held by General
Motors Corp. and the fashion community to raise money to fight
breast cancer.
</P>
<P>
   The automaker did not know Johnson had the disease when it asked
her to participate in the event by decorating a Chevy Cavalier
being raffled off for charity.
</P>
<P>
   ''I just hope all my customers and girls will get earlier
mammograms and checkups. I feel it's time to give back, if there's
anything I can give,'' she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
