<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 13:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-Royal Aide Plans Diana Memoir  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- To the dismay of Queen Elizabeth II and Prince
Charles, a former royal aide plans to publish a memoir about his
years working with Princess Diana.
</P>
<P>
   The book by Patrick Jephson, Diana's private secretary, will
cover 1987 to 1996 -- a particularly troubled time in the princess's
life. She and Charles separated in 1992 and divorced in 1996.
</P>
<P>
   ''Whatever its possible content, the book is likely to arouse
fresh speculation about the life of the princess which can only be
upsetting to the feelings of Prince William and Prince Harry, and
to the princess's family,'' the queen and Prince Charles said
Friday in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   Jephson promised a ''truthful and balanced account'' and said he
is sure the royal family will be reassured when they read the book.
</P>
<P>
   ''Since her death I have been dismayed by the indiscriminate
comment she has received, much of it inaccurate, some of it
apparently intended to diminish her memory,'' Jephson said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
   Diana died in 1997 in a Paris car accident.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
