<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 17:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Friday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
   
NYSE
</P>
<P>
   Xerox, up $1.88 to $17.88
</P>
<P>
   Shares of the struggling copier company moved higher after a
published report that it was being eyed for acquisition by Hewlett
Packard, Cannon and others.
</P>
<P>
   Maytag, down $2.19 at $33.63
</P>
<P>
   The home appliance maker warned that its second-half results
will be lower than expected because of the loss of two major
customers.
</P>
<P>
   Metals USA, down 1.25 cents to $3.56
</P>
<P>
   The metals-processing company warned late Thursday its
third-quarter earnings will be below Wall Street expectations.
</P>
<P>
   
Nasdaq
</P>
<P>
   Electric Fuel, up $2.19 at $11.88
</P>
<P>
   The maker of electric vehicle battery systems said it has a
contract with the government of Germany to develop an all-electric
hybrid vehicle.
</P>
