<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Skydiver making night jump killed, found away from his parachute  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WANTAGE, N.J. (AP) - Aviation officials are investigating the
death of an Italian skydiver whose body was found about a
quarter-mile from his parachute after a night jump, authorities
said.
</P>
<P>
   State Police recovered the body of Gianni Lattarico, 24, in a
wooded area at 12:45 p.m. Friday, while his parachute was found in
some trees, State Police Sgt. Al Della Fave said.
</P>
<P>
   Lattarico, who is from Italy, was part of a team of four
skydivers who left from Sussex Airport Thursday night to make a
jump that would qualify them to regularly parachute at night, Della
Fave said.
</P>
<P>
   Lattarico was the last of the four to jump at 9:15 p.m.
Thursday, and should have landed four minutes later, Della Fave
said.
</P>
<P>
   The cause of the accident is under investigation. Federal
Aviation Administration officials will send an inspector to
determine whether Lattarico's parachute was packed correctly,
spokeswoman Arlene Salac said.
</P>
</TEXT>
