<TEXT>
<P>
 Friday, Sept. 15, 2000
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
U.S. Wins 1st Gold Medal in Sydney
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- American Nancy Johnson captured the first gold
medal of the Sydney Olympics, firing her way to victory Saturday (Friday night
EDT) in the women's 10-meter air rifle. The silver medal went to Kang Cho-Hyun
of South Korea, while Gao Jing of China took the bronze. It was the first of 13
medal events on Day 1 of full competition.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Deal Set on Debate Formats
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Democrat Al Gore and Republican George W. Bush tentatively
agreed today on three debate formats -- one traditional two-lectern event, one
town hall, and one ''talk show'' forum -- said officials close to negotiations.
The two campaigns, after meeting 7&AMP;frac12; hours, planned to meet again Saturday
to complete details and sign off on the formats, said one official close to
debate negotiations.
</P>
