Albright Attends Afghanistan Meeting
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   UNITED NATIONS (AP) -- Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and Iranian
Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi attended a closed-door meeting Friday on
Afghanistan, an encounter which U.S. officials hope will be an ''ice breaker''
in U.S.-Iranian relations. The United States and Iran are members of an
eight-country group that has been working to end the long civil war in the
central Asian nation and advance the peace process.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Al Gore Seeks Black Support
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Appealing to a standing-room-only crowd and a group of
potential voters who overwhelmingly back him, Democrat Al Gore made a campaign
pitch today to students at a historically black university, ''We want Gore! We
want Gore!'' the Howard University audience chanted, waving blue and white
pompoms and Gore-Lieberman signs. With solid black support, the presidential
nominee's focus is boosting turnout among a group that has not gone to the polls
as often as whites.
</P>
