McCain Proposes Tire Legislation
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- A bill introduced in the Senate today would require
automakers and their suppliers to share much more safety information with the
federal government and significantly strengthen penalties for those that
withhold key data. The legislation, introduced by Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz., is
at least the fifth addressing issues uncovered in the Firestone tire
investigation, but it is the first scheduled for congressional action. McCain
said he hoped to pass it out of his Senate Commerce Committee on Wednesday.
</P>
