Swiss Triathlete Wins Gold
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Brigitte McMahon of Switzerland won the Olympic
gold medal Saturday (Friday night EDT) in the woman's triathlon, finishing in a
time of 2 hours, 40 seconds. Michellie Jones of Australia won the silver and
Magali Messmer of Switzerland the bronze.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Indiana Trustees Pass Conduct Code
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   NEW ALBANY, Ind. (AP) -- Reacting to the behavior that cost Bob Knight his
job, Indiana's trustees adopted a code of conduct today requiring coaches and
athletes to treat others with dignity and respect. An 11-page report spelling
out the behavior the university expects from participants in its sports programs
was developed by a commission created in May in conjunction with the
zero-tolerance behavior policy Knight agreed to at the time to keep his job.
</P>
