<HEADLINE> 3 Italians Kidnapped in Colombia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEDELLIN, Colombia (AP) -- Gunmen kidnapped three Italians on
Friday as they drove on a main Colombian highway, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities blamed rebels of the National Liberation Army for
kidnaping the men, who Italian news report said are electricians
working for the National Chocolate Factory in Rio Negro, near
Medellin.
</P>
<P>
   Police said the Italians were intercepted by a pickup truck
carrying five men on the Medellin-Bogota highway.
</P>
<P>
   Rebels are believed responsible for 60 percent of the
kidnappings that occur in Colombia, which has one of the world's
highest kidnapping rates.
</P>
<P>
   Through July of 2000, 1,754 people were kidnapped in Colombia.
</P>
