<HEADLINE> Lagretto Wins World Cup Event  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEVON, Pa. (AP) -- Lagretto, ridden by Kate Levy of Katonah,
N.Y., cleared all seven barriers without a fault in the tiebreaking
round to win the opening event of the American Gold Cup Equestrian
Festival on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   The win for the 13-year-old Belgian-bred gelding and his
20-year-old owner/rider came on the heels of a victory Saturday in
the Autumn Classic Horse Show in Port Jervis, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   Levy and Lagretto topped the 48 starters by winning a two-horse
jumpoff over Olympic champion Leslie Burr-Howard of Westport,
Conn., astride the Irish-bred Clover Leaf.
</P>
<P>
   Levy and Burr-Howard were the only two riders to ride their
mounts to fault-free scores over 17 jumps within the 83-second time
allowed in the first round of the qualifier.
</P>
<P>
   Lagretto and Levy posted a score of zero faults in 38.23
seconds, well within the 43-second time allowed.
</P>
<P>
   Clover Leaf dropped the top rail from the third barrier on the
course for four faults. He finished with eight jumping faults and
two time faults.
</P>
<P>
   Levy and Lagretto earned the right to start in the coveted and
last place in the 40-horse jumping order, one ahead of Clover Leaf
and Burr-Howard, in Sunday's $60,000 American Gold Cup Grand Prix.
</P>
</TEXT>
