<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blue Jays 6, White Sox 5  </HEADLINE>
By RICK GANO
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Alex Gonzalez and Darrin Fletcher homered off
struggling Chicago rookie Jon Garland and the Toronto Blue Jays
continued their strong play at Comiskey Park, beating the White Sox
6-5 Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Blue Jays, three games behind Cleveland in the AL wild card
chase, have won seven of their last nine games at Comiskey, dating
back to 1998. Cleveland beat New York 11-1.
</P>
<P>
   Chicago's loss left the White Sox's magic number at 11 for
clinching the AL Central.
</P>
<P>
   In a meeting of MVP candidates, Toronto's Carlos Delgado walked
twice and was hit by a pitch in an 0-for-1 night while Chicago's
Frank Thomas was 0-for-4 with a walk.
</P>
<P>
   Toronto drove Garland (3-7) out in the fifth on run-scoring
doubles by Brad Fullmer and Fletcher that made it 6-2. Fletcher hit
a solo homer in the fourth, his 18th.
</P>
<P>
   The 20-year-old Garland, the youngest pitcher in the majors,
hasn't made it past the fifth inning in three starts since coming
off the disabled list 11 days ago. He gave up six hits, including
two homers, and six runs -- four earned -- with five walks.
</P>
<P>
   Jose Valentin's two-run homer in the fifth, his 23rd, cut the
lead to 6-4 and was Chicago's club-record 199th homer this season.
Charles Johnson hit a solo shot, his 28th, off John Frascatore to
make it 6-5 in the seventh.
</P>
<P>
   Kelvim Escobar (10-14) retired Thomas and Magglio Ordonez with a
runner on to end the seventh and pitched a scoreless eighth. Billy
Koch got three outs for his 33rd save, including Thomas on a
strikeout with the tying run on third base.
</P>
<P>
   The Blue Jays scored three in the third as Shannon Stewart
reached on an error when Sox first baseman Paul Konerko couldn't
handle his hard grounder and Gonzalez followed with his 13th homer.
Dave Martinez walked, moved up on a grounder and scored on
Fullmer's single.
</P>
<P>
   Chicago loaded the bases with no outs in the third on two walks
and Magglio Ordonez's single but managed just one run on Carlos
Lee's RBI single as Quantrill got Paul Konerko on a 5-2-3 double
play.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson had an RBI single for Chicago's first run in the third
off starter Steve Trachsel, who lasted just three plus innings.
Notes: Fall was in the air with a 62-degree game-time temperature.
... Cal Eldred, still trying to see if can pitch again this season
with a screw in his elbow, made 40 tosses from 40-to-50 feet Friday
with no pain. He'll throw again Sunday. Eldred has a stress
fracture of his elbow and has been on the DL since July. He had
surgery to implant the screw last week. ... The 1998 White Sox hit
198 homers. ... Delgado is homerless in his last 16 games, his
longest drought this season. ... Mark Buehrle pitched 3 1-3 hitless
innings of relief for the White Sox.
</P>
</TEXT>
